SIMPLE: consequentially
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Consequentially
<hw>Con`se*quen"tial*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>With just
deduction of consequence; with right connection of ideas;
logically.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The faculty of writing <qex>consequentially</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>By remote consequence; not immediately; eventually;
<as>as, to do a thing <ex>consequentially</ex></as>.</def>
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In a regular series; in the order of cause and
effect; with logical concatenation; consecutively;
continuously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>With assumed importance; pompously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Consequentialness</ent>⟦br⟧
